The iOS PDF text-to-speech feature uses Apple APIs to guess the language of the document. By default, the language is automatically detected using a framework function provided by Apple. This works for many documents but sometimes guesses wrong. If you know the language of the document, we suggest setting it manually using the [`selectedLanguage`][] property of the [`PSPDFSpeechController`][], which can be accessed via the [shared PSPDFKitGlobal configuration instance][pspdfkitglobal.sharedinstance]:

[==

```swift
PSPDFKitGlobal.sharedInstance.speechController.selectedLanguage = documentLanguage
```

```objc
PSPDFKitGlobal.sharedInstance.speechController.selectedLanguage = documentLanguage;
```

==]

The [`PSPDFSpeechController`][] has additional properties to control speed rate and pitch.

